# No middleware in a static export, so redirect locale-less section paths to the
# default locale at the Cloudflare edge. Each locale's pages are served directly
# (/en, /id). The bare section paths keep external links locale-agnostic — e.g.
# the host nav links to `<blog>/cv`, which lands on /en/cv (see ../../docs/deployment.md).
#
# The apex `/` is deliberately NOT redirected here — it serves app/page.tsx,
# which detects the visitor's browser language client-side and routes to /en or
# /id (the edge can't read Accept-Language on a static export). See that file.
/cv        /en/cv       302
/posts     /en/posts    302
